Ms. H. Thi Bich Lien, born in 1965, Ms 10040047, loan amount requesting is 121 USD to invest in her general store. Her husband is a soldier, and her 2 children are of school-age. Her family has a general store to serve the local village, selling items such as fertilizer, rice, tea, beer, liquor, cakes, candy.. She also supplement her production by raising livestock. Her family's average income is from 6 - 9 USD per day. Her sources of daily income agree with the weekly loan repayment schedule. 

Other members requesting loan with her are:
Ms. N. Thi Hang; born in 1969, Ms 10040048, loan amount requesting 121 USD to invest in her barber shop;
Ms. Hoan Thi Bich Diu, born in 1975, Ms 10040049, loan amount requesting 121 USD to raise chickens;
Ms. D. Thi Hiep, born in 1965, Ms 10040050, loan amount requesting 121 USD to raise ducks, chickens, groose;
Ms. N. Thi Kim Oanh, born in 1978, Ms 100400, loan amount requesting 121 USD to purchase vegetables/produce;
Ms. N. Thi Cam, born in 1974, Ms 10040051, loan amount requesting 120 USD to invest in her tailor shop





.<br /><p><strong>Translated from Vietnamese by Thu Ostrander, Kiva Volunteer</strong></p>

Ms. N. Thi Quy, born in 1952 ( Ms 05030019 ), loan amount requesting 240 USD to invest in her souvenir shop. She lives with her husband and children in the hamlet of Hoi Phu, Dong Anh, Ha Noi. Her husband and children also work to supplement their income and better their lives. Her famiL.'s average income is 270 USD per month. She is a hard-working person. In addition to her shop, whenever they have free time, her famiL. also makes straw brooms to sell. In her group of loan members, she is the eldest and is the leader of the group. The other members are

Ms. N. Thi Nhien, born in 1963 ( Ms 05030016 ), loan amount requesting 240 USD to invest in her retail shop;
